Actor Woody Harrelson is heading to a galaxy far, far away for his next movie, playing a role in the second anthology Star Wars film focused on a young Han Solo. Lucasfilm said on Wednesday that the 55-year-old Oscar-nominated actor will join Alden Ehrenreich, who will play the younger version of the smuggler and space pirate Han Solo. The cast will also include Donald Glover, as a young Lando Calrissian, and Emilia Clarke, of Game of Thrones, in an undisclosed role. The Hunger Games actor told Mashable in a Facebook Live that he would be playing a mentor to Han, but I m also a bit of a criminal . He added: I don t think I should say much more than that, because the Force is not allowing me. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.